    {
      "id": "18f4750c-f3ba-80b9-9a06-c7d19116dc75",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The ability to reach tutors or peers is often hindered in MOOCs in comparison to traditional settings. The authors look to identify different types of help-seeking behavior in MOOCs from Melbourne University. To do that, they use different unsupervised techniques (affinity propagation clustering and t-SNE). Authors identify 5 patterns of help-seeking behavior and evaluate the relationship of these profiles with performance.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "18f4750c-f3ba-80b9-9a06-c7d19116dc75",
        "parent": {
